# Render Static Frontend Deploy

Source: `render.yaml` static site services + product frontend layout

## Monorepo layout

Product frontends (`apps/*-frontend`) import `@stl/shared-ui` via **tsconfig paths** and **Vite alias** to `packages/shared-ui/src`. TypeScript type-checks those source files during `tsc -b`.

Render runs `npm ci` in each app's `rootDir` only. **`packages/shared-ui/node_modules` is not installed** unless the build command installs it.

## Tailwind v4 + aliased shared-ui

Product `index.css` must tell Tailwind to scan shared shell sources, or layout utilities used only in `@stl/shared-ui` (`flex-col`, `w-64`, `min-w-0`, `shrink-0`, etc.) are omitted from the production CSS bundle — the shell collapses to a horizontal product row and a narrow main column.

```css
@import 'tailwindcss';

@source "../../../packages/shared-ui/src";
```

After changing shared-ui shell classes, rebuild every product frontend and confirm `dist/assets/*.css` includes `flex-col` and `w-64`.

## Vite: single React instance (product frontends)

When aliasing `@stl/shared-ui` to source, add `resolve.dedupe` so shared-ui and the app share one `react` / `react-dom` / `react-router-dom`. Without it, authenticated shells crash at runtime (`Cannot read properties of null (reading 'useContext')`) and the page stays blank after handoff.

```ts
resolve: {
  dedupe: ['react', 'react-dom', 'react-router-dom'],
  alias: {
    '@stl/shared-ui': path.resolve(appRoot, '../../packages/shared-ui/src'),
  },
},
```

## Required buildCommand (product frontends using shared-ui)

```yaml
buildCommand: npm ci --prefix ../../packages/shared-ui && npm ci && npm run build
```

Applies to: `staffarr-frontend`, `trainarr-frontend`, `maintainarr-frontend`, `routarr-frontend`, `supplyarr-frontend`, `compliancecore-frontend`, `companion-frontend`.

`suite-frontend` does not use `@stl/shared-ui`; keep `npm ci && npm run build`.

## Pre-push checklist (touched frontends)

1. **`package-lock.json` committed** in the app dir and in `packages/shared-ui` when deps change.
2. **`rootDir` matches** `apps/<product>-frontend` in `render.yaml`.
3. **`VITE_*` env vars** set in `render.yaml` for any value read at build time.
4. **Reproduce Render locally** from the app directory:
   ```bash
   npm ci --prefix ../../packages/shared-ui
   npm ci
   npm run build
   npm run preview
   ```
   Smoke: unauthenticated visit shows sign-in guidance; after suite handoff, topbar + sidebar shell render (not an empty `#root`).
5. **`render.yaml`**: `staticPublishPath: dist`, SPA rewrite `/*` → `/index.html`, and `VITE_SUITE_URL` / product API `VITE_*` for build-time env.
6. After changing `packages/shared-ui`, rebuild **every** product frontend that imports it.

## Common failure signatures

| Log error | Cause |
|-----------|--------|
| `Cannot find module 'react'` in `../../packages/shared-ui/src/...` | shared-ui deps not installed before `tsc -b` |
| `react/jsx-runtime` missing in shared-ui | Same as above |
| `npm ci` EUSAGE / lock out of sync | Missing or stale `package-lock.json` |
| Unused import TS6133 in `*.test.tsx` | Strict `noUnusedLocals`; remove or use the import |
| Blank page after launch; console `useContext` null | Missing `resolve.dedupe` for React when bundling aliased shared-ui |
| Horizontal product row, empty center, narrow main | Missing `@source` for `packages/shared-ui/src` in product `index.css` |
